Considerations When Converting Query Types

CRM Analytics treats query types differently. Before you convert an aggregate or aggregateflex query type to saql, review the following implications.

Unlike the aggregateflex query type, the saql query type provides limited support when the actual number of query results exceeds the limit that a query can return.

When performing a search in a list widget, a saql query type doesn’t find values that aren’t returned in the first batch of query results.
CRM Analytics doesn’t apply initial selections for a saql query type if the selected value isn’t returned in the first batch of query results.
